        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 9:08PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 907 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Walsh, or 12 miles west of The Saunders Elevator,
moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Walsh and Stonington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
southeastern Colorado.</instruction>
